## What I Learned About Project Organization

I learned how to organize my files properly inside a repository. I created a folder called Day1 and placed all required files inside it with the correct names. I understood that naming is case-sensitive and must be exactly as required.

This helped me realize the importance of clean structure and organization when working on projects.

---

## Conclusion

Overall, today I learned the fundamentals of C programming and the basics of using Git and GitHub. I now understand how to create and run simple programs, manage my code using branches, and keep my project organized. These skills are very important and will help me continue working more efficiently during the internship.

